		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">Minard Hamilton is head of sales and marketing for EA Mobile and was executive vice president of sales and marketing at JAMDAT Mobile, which was acquired by Electronic Arts in February 2006.  Prior to joining JAMDAT in 2001, Hamilton was the general manager at ESPN.com International where he oversaw the building of their businesses in Europe, Latin America and Asia.  Hamilton also served as a senior vice president at ESPN International Television. Besides overseeing ESPN's international networks, Hamilton handled relationships with the NBA, NFL, MLB, the Premier League, Serie A and UEFA.  Early in his career, Hamilton was head of worldwide distribution and acquisitions at Roger Corman's Concorde-New Horizons, Inc., where he also produced several films. Hamilton holds a B.A. from Princeton University and an MBA from the Anderson Graduate School of Management at UCLA.</span></td>
